  "text": "OpenTelemetry Span Creation Patterns Across Prometheus and Grafana\n\nPROMETHEUS (8 files):\n- prometheus/tracing/tracing.go: Central tracer provider initialization with Manager class that builds and manages TracerProvider lifecycle using SDK with OTLP exporters (gRPC/HTTP), resource configuration with semantic conventions, and sampling setup.\n- prometheus/promql/engine.go: Demonstrates span creation with otel.Tracer(\"\").Start() for query evaluation, span attribute setting with SetAttributes() for query expressions, and span event addition with AddEvent() for expand operations.\n- prometheus/storage/remote/queue_manager.go: Shows tracer initialization with otel.Tracer(\"\"), batch span creation with SetAttributes() for metadata/sample counts/remote endpoint info, error recording with span.RecordError(), semantic convention usage (semconv.HTTPResendCount), and span lifecycle with defer span.End().\n- prometheus/scrape/scrape.go: Tracer usage with otel.Tracer(\"\").Start() and WithSpanKind option, integration with otelhttp for HTTP client tracing through otelhttptrace.\n- prometheus/storage/remote/client.go: Client-side span creation with trace.WithSpanKind(trace.SpanKindClient) and otelhttp integration.\n- prometheus/rules/group.go: Rule group span creation and tracer initialization with otel imports.\n- prometheus/util/stats/query_stats.go: Tracer.Start() and span.End() usage for operation tracking.\n- prometheus/scrape/scrape_test.go: Test setup with sdktrace.NewTracerProvider and AlwaysSample() for testing.\n\nGRAFANA (10+ key files from 265 total):\n- pkg/infra/tracing/tracing.go: Central TracingService with tracer provider initialization through initOpentelemetryTracer(), supporting both Jaeger (agent/collector) and OTLP protocols. Uses tracesdk.NewTracerProvider with Batcher, Resource (semconv), and Sampler configuration.\n- apps/dashboard/pkg/migration/conversion/metrics.go: Tracer initialization with otel.GetTracerProvider().Tracer(\"dashboard-converter\"), span creation with tracer.Start(), lifecycle management with defer span.End(), attribute setting with SetAttributes(), and error recording with span.RecordError().\n- apps/iam/pkg/reconcilers/folder_reconciler.go: Complete span lifecycle: otel.GetTracerProvider().Tracer() initialization, start with trace.WithAttributes() for action/folder/namespace, span.RecordError(), span.SetStatus() with codes.Error.\n- apps/dashboard/pkg/migration/conversion/tracing_helper.go: Helper function TracingStart() for reusable span creation pattern using trace.SpanFromContext().TracerProvider().Tracer().Start().\n- Multiple conversion files (v0alpha1_to_v1beta1.go, v1beta1_to_v2alpha1.go, etc.): Consistent usage of defer span.End() and span.SetAttributes() for schema version tracking.\n- pkg/api/api.go, pkg/api/utils.go: HTTP request span injection with injectSpan() helper.\n- pkg/middleware/request_tracing.go: HTTP middleware-level span creation.\n- apps/alerting/historian/pkg/app/app.go, apps/iam/pkg/reconcilers/zanzana_service.go: Service-layer span creation.\n\nKEY PATTERNS IDENTIFIED:\n\n1. TRACER INITIALIZATION:\n   - Prometheus: Manager class with buildTracerProvider() creates tracesdk.TracerProvider with Batcher, Resource, and Sampler\n   - Grafana: TracingService.initOpentelemetryTracer() with separate paths for Jaeger and OTLP, using tracesdk.NewTracerProvider()\n   - Both: otel.SetTracerProvider() to register globally\n\n2. SPAN START/END:\n   - Prometheus: ctx, span := otel.Tracer(\"\").Start(ctx, name) with defer span.End()\n   - Grafana: tracer := otel.GetTracerProvider().Tracer(name) followed by ctx, span := tracer.Start(ctx, name) with defer span.End()\n\n3. SPAN OPTIONS:\n   - Prometheus: trace.WithSpanKind(trace.SpanKindClient) for client spans, trace.WithAttributes() for event attributes\n   - Grafana: trace.WithAttributes() for initial span attributes\n\n4. ATTRIBUTE SETTING:\n   - Both use span.SetAttributes(attribute.String/Int/Float64(...))\n   - Prometheus: attribute keys like \"query\", \"operation\", \"selector\", \"num_series\"\n   - Grafana: attribute keys like \"dashboard.uid\", \"folder.uid\", \"action\", \"datasource.type\"\n\n5. ERROR RECORDING:\n   - Both: span.RecordError(err) for error capture\n   - Grafana: Also uses span.SetStatus(codes.Error, message)\n\n6. EVENT RECORDING:\n   - Prometheus: span.AddEvent() with optional trace.WithAttributes()\n   - Example: span.AddEvent(\"expand start\", trace.WithAttributes(...))\n\n7. SEMANTIC CONVENTIONS:\n   - Prometheus: semconv.HTTPResendCount() for HTTP-specific attributes\n   - Grafana: semconv package usage in resource configuration\n\n8. EXPORTERS:\n   - Prometheus: otlptracegrpc.NewClient, otlptracehttp.NewClient with TLS, headers, timeout, compression options\n   - Grafana: Both Jaeger exporter (agent/collector modes) and OTLP with similar configuration options\n\n9. RESOURCE CONFIGURATION:\n   - Both: resource.New() with ServiceName, ServiceVersion via semconv\n   - WithProcessRuntimeDescription(), WithTelemetrySDK() in Prometheus\n   - WithCustomAttribs in Grafana\n\n10. SAMPLING:\n    - Prometheus: tracesdk.ParentBased(tracesdk.TraceIDRatioBased(samplingFraction))\n    - Grafana: Remote sampler support via initSampler()"
}

